-- Greek 10-Year Bond Premium to German Bunds Declines Below 500 Basis Points
-- Paul Dobson
-- 2010-04-23T10:00:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/greek-10-year-bond-premium-to-german-bunds-declines-below-500-basis-points.html

          
          
             The yield premium investors demand
to hold Greek 10-year bonds instead of benchmark German bunds
slid to less than 500 basis points as of 10:58 a.m. in London,
from 590 basis points, which was the highest since at least
March 1998, when Bloomberg began compiling the generic prices.  
